										<td class="py-3 pr-4">Email address of the adult providing consent on behalf of a user under 13 (and, as a contractual condition, for users under 18); confirmation of consent.</td>
										<td class="py-3">Directly from the adult.</td>
									</tr>
								</tbody>
							</table>
						</div>
						<p class="mb-4 mt-4">
							The user (or the adult, where applicable) may choose not to provide certain personal data, which may limit access to features of the App.
						</p>
						<p>
							We may also collect, use and disclose aggregate or de-identified data that cannot identify an individual, for any purpose. Such data is not considered personal data.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">5. Processing of minors' personal data</h3>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.1. Age of consent</h4>
						<p class="mb-4">
							In Portugal, the minimum age for a minor to give valid consent to the processing of personal data in connection with information society services is 13 years (Article 16 of Law No. 58/2019). Where a user is under 13, processing of their personal data is only lawful with the consent of the holder of parental responsibility, which We collect and verify through email confirmation sent to the adult at the time of registration.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Where a user is 13 or older, they may give consent themselves; however, as a contractual condition of access to the App under our Terms &amp; Conditions, all users under 18 must use the App with the knowledge and consent of a parent or legal guardian, verified through the same email confirmation process.
						</p>
						<p>
							Where data concerning health is shared through the chat, processing is based on explicit consent, given by the user aged 13 or over and/or by the holder of parental responsibility, as applicable.
						</p>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.2. Age verification</h4>
						<p>
							At registration, users are required to provide their date of birth. This information is used to determine the applicable consent requirements and to restrict access to age-appropriate content and features. Users aged 16 to 18 may have access to content or features not available to users aged 12 to 15.
						</p>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">5.3. Parental rights</h4>
						<p>
							If You are the parent or legal guardian of a minor who has provided personal data without proper consent, You may contact us using the details in Section 2 to request its removal.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">6. Cookies and similar technologies</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							The App uses cookies and similar technologies, including device identifiers and mechanisms that store or read information on the device (such as SDKs). These technologies allow the App to function properly and, where You consent, to analyze usage and improve Your experience.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">Categories:</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li><strong>Strictly necessary:</strong> essential for the proper functioning of the App and for providing the services You request. These do not require consent.</li>
							<li><strong>Analytics and functional:</strong> used to understand how users interact with the App and to remember preferences. These are only set after You have given Your consent.</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Consent mechanism: on Your first use of the App, You are presented with a mechanism allowing You to accept or reject non-essential technologies, with both options given equal prominence. No non-essential technology is set before You make a choice. You may withdraw or change Your consent at any time through the settings available within the App.
						</p>
						<p>
							You can also manage these technologies through Your device settings. Disabling certain technologies may affect the proper functioning of the App.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">7. Use of the chat</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							The chat is a private, one-to-one feature (between the user and MÔÇES), available to registered users for general informational guidance, clarification of doubts about the content, and sharing of opinions. It is not operated as a clinical service and does not provide psychological, medical or emergency services.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Messages submitted through the chat may contain data concerning health and are processed on the basis of the user's explicit consent (and that of the holder of parental responsibility, where applicable). They may be retained for a limited period for quality assurance, safety monitoring and recordkeeping purposes, unless the user requests their deletion earlier. MÔÇES may remove messages that violate the Terms &amp; Conditions or contact users for clarifications related to chat usage.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							The chat must not be used in emergencies. If You or someone You know is in crisis, please contact the relevant emergency or mental health services.
						</p>

						<h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-3 mt-6">Contact with a professional</h4>
						<p class="mb-4">
							The chat may involve interaction with a psychology professional, a member of staff employed by MÔÇES under a contract of employment, acting within the scope of their duties and on behalf of the association. No clinical, therapeutic or crisis services are provided through the chat.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Where digital contact involves the exchange of personal or sensitive information with a psychology professional, MÔÇES will request prior informed consent, covering: the purpose of the communication; the categories of data collected; the means and period of storage; the security measures adopted; the risks associated with digital communication; and the user's rights under the GDPR. Where the user is under 13, consent must be given by the adult.
						</p>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Identity verification may be required to ensure the safety and appropriateness of the support provided.
						</p>
						<p>
							Risk situations: if, in the context of the chat, a serious risk to the life or physical integrity of the user or a third party is identified, MÔÇES may contact the competent services on the basis of the protection of vital interests [Article 9(2)(c) GDPR].
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">8. Data retention periods</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							We retain personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes described in this Notice:
						</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2">
							<li><strong>Account and registration data:</strong> for as long as the account remains active and for no longer than 1 year following account deletion or inactivity.</li>
							<li><strong>Chat messages (including any health data):</strong> for as long as necessary for quality assurance, safety and recordkeeping purposes and, in any event, for no longer than 1 year, unless a longer retention period is required by legal or professional obligation. The user may request deletion of their messages at any time, subject to any overriding obligation.</li>
							<li><strong>Parental consent records:</strong> for as long as the user's account is active, plus the period required to demonstrate compliance with applicable law.</li>
							<li><strong>Technical and usage data:</strong> for as long as necessary for the purpose of processing and, in any event, for no longer than 1 year, except where a longer period is required or permitted by law.</li>
							<li><strong>Data subject to legal retention obligations</strong> (e.g., accounting or tax records, where applicable): for the period prescribed by applicable law, which may exceed the periods above.</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">9. Data subject rights</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							Under the GDPR, users (and, where the user is a minor, their parent or legal guardian) have the following rights:
						</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2">
							<li>To be informed about the source, purposes and legal bases of processing and the identity of the controller;</li>
							<li>To access personal data and obtain a copy;</li>
							<li>To rectify inaccurate personal data;</li>
							<li>To erase personal data, where no overriding obligation to retain it exists;</li>
							<li>To restrict or object to processing;</li>
							<li>To data portability, where processing is based on consent or contract and carried out by automated means;</li>
							<li>To withdraw consent at any time, without affecting the lawfulness of processing carried out before withdrawal;</li>
							<li>To lodge a complaint with the Comissão Nacional de Proteção de Dados (CNPD), Av. D. Carlos I, 134, 1.º, 1200-651 Lisboa, <a href="https://www.cnpd.pt" class="text-black hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.cnpd.pt</a>, or with the supervisory authority of the user's habitual residence, place of work, or place of the alleged infringement.</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mt-4">
							Some of these rights may be restricted where We have a legitimate interest or a legal obligation to continue processing, or where the data is covered by confidentiality or professional secrecy.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">10. International data transfers</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							To provide the App's services, We rely on the following processors, some of which process personal data outside the European Economic Area (EEA):
						</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li>Supabase (database and authentication), with servers located in the United Kingdom;</li>
							<li>Resend (transactional email delivery), based in the United States;</li>
							<li>Firebase / Google (usage analytics), which may involve the processing of personal data in the United States.</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mb-4">
							In such cases, We ensure that the transfer is subject to appropriate safeguards under Chapter V of the GDPR (Articles 44 to 49), namely a European Commission adequacy decision, Standard Contractual Clauses or, for certified providers in the United States, the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, namely:
						</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li>With respect to the United Kingdom (Supabase): the transfer is covered by the European Commission's adequacy decision concerning the United Kingdom, renewed on 19 December 2025 and valid until 27 December 2031, meaning no supplementary safeguards are required;</li>
							<li>With respect to the United States (Resend and, where applicable, Firebase/Google): the transfer relies on the respective providers' certification under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (DPF).</li>
						</ul>
						<p>
							Users may request further information about the applicable safeguards using the details in Section 2.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">11. Disclosure of data to third parties</h3>
						<p class="mb-4">
							We do not transfer personal data to third parties unless required by applicable law, at the request of the data subject, or in the other cases set out in this Notice. We disclose personal data to third parties only where necessary for the purposes described here or where required by law, namely to:
						</p>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside ml-4 mt-2 space-y-2 mb-4">
							<li>
								Service providers acting as processors on our behalf (e.g., hosting, App infrastructure), under a data processing agreement in accordance with Article 28 GDPR, namely to:
								<ul class="list-[circle] list-inside ml-6 mt-2 space-y-1">
									<li>Dengun, responsible for the technical development and maintenance of the App, with access to the database and backoffice in connection with that service;</li>
									<li>Supabase, for database hosting and authentication;</li>
									<li>Resend, for transactional email delivery;</li>
									<li>Firebase/Google, for App usage analytics;</li>
								</ul>
							</li>
							<li>Competent authorities, where required by applicable law or in response to lawful requests by judicial, law enforcement or regulatory bodies.</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mb-4">
							All parties with access to users' personal data are bound to comply with applicable data protection legislation and to maintain confidentiality.
						</p>
						<p>
							The App may contain links to other websites (for informational purposes only). When navigating to other websites through these links, this Notice no longer applies, and We recommend reviewing their privacy policies before providing any personal data.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">12. Security of personal data</h3>
						<p>
							We use widely accepted standards of technological and operational protection to prevent the loss, misuse, alteration or destruction of data. However, We do not guarantee absolute protection against threats beyond our control. We recommend that users do not use unprotected channels to transmit confidential information to us.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[#111827] mb-4">13. Changes to this Privacy Notice</h3>
						<p>
							We may update this Notice from time to time by publishing a revised version within the App. Where changes materially affect how We process personal data, We will notify users by reasonable means. Where renewed consent is required by law, We will request it separately. The "Last updated" date indicates when this Notice was last revised.
						</p>
